Yes.

837
00:35:51,200 --> 00:35:51,440
Alright.

838
00:35:51,600 --> 00:35:51,920
Good.

839
00:35:58,960 --> 00:35:59,840
Runzhi,

840
00:36:00,160 --> 00:36:00,560
right?

841
00:36:01,040 --> 00:36:01,440
Yes.

842
00:36:02,320 --> 00:36:04,800
Working in the library is hard work.

843
00:36:05,200 --> 00:36:06,640
Sometimes we have to work overtime.

844
00:36:06,960 --> 00:36:08,240
If you stay late you may just stay here for the night.

845
00:36:08,320 --> 00:36:09,120
There's blankets there.

846
00:36:09,280 --> 00:36:10,000
No need to worry.

847
00:36:10,160 --> 00:36:10,560
Thank you.

848
00:36:10,720 --> 00:36:11,520
No problem.

849
00:36:13,680 --> 00:36:15,040
Do you enjoy reading?

850
00:36:15,840 --> 00:36:16,400
I do!

851
00:36:17,120 --> 00:36:17,520
I...

852
00:36:17,760 --> 00:36:19,040
like to read every genre.

853
00:36:19,520 --> 00:36:20,960
What books are you reading recently?

854
00:36:21,680 --> 00:36:22,480
Recently,

855
00:36:22,640 --> 00:36:23,280
I have enjoyed reading

856
00:36:23,520 --> 00:36:24,560
books on anarchism.

857
00:36:28,480 --> 00:36:29,360
In this case,

858
00:36:29,920 --> 00:36:31,760
you're a follower of anarchism?

859
00:36:32,320 --> 00:36:33,440
I won't call myself a follower,

860
00:36:33,760 --> 00:36:34,800
I'm just interested

861
00:36:35,120 --> 00:36:35,760
out of curiosity.

862
00:36:38,880 --> 00:36:39,520
Runzhi,

863
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:41,280
pass me that book please.

864
00:36:41,760 --> 00:36:42,160
Alright.

865
00:36:43,920 --> 00:36:45,120
Here.

866
00:36:45,760 --> 00:36:46,960
"The Communist Manifesto"

867
00:36:48,000 --> 00:36:48,800
Have you read it?

868
00:36:50,320 --> 00:36:51,200
I've heard of it,

869
00:36:51,920 --> 00:36:53,040
but I haven't read it.

870
00:36:55,360 --> 00:36:55,760
Then,

871
00:36:56,400 --> 00:36:57,840
how about the Russia's October Revolution?

872
00:36:59,120 --> 00:37:00,080
I've heard about it as well,

873
00:37:00,480 --> 00:37:01,360
but I'm not sure.

874
00:37:02,320 --> 00:37:03,040
It's alright.

875
00:37:04,160 --> 00:37:05,120
After today,

876
00:37:05,440 --> 00:37:07,760
we will be clear on it.

877
00:37:12,160 --> 00:37:13,040
This side's almost done.

878
00:37:13,200 --> 00:37:13,440
Runzhi,

879
00:37:13,840 --> 00:37:15,600
let's move this shelf over there.

880
00:37:15,840 --> 00:37:16,080
Alright.

881
00:37:17,920 --> 00:37:18,800
Be careful of the books on top.

882
00:37:18,880 --> 00:37:19,600
Slowly.

883
00:37:25,840 --> 00:37:26,560
Lift it up.

884
00:37:27,520 --> 00:37:28,240
Give me a hand.

885
00:37:28,320 --> 00:37:28,960
One, two, three.

886
00:37:29,280 --> 00:37:29,520
Alright.

887
00:37:30,080 --> 00:37:30,640
This way.

888
00:37:37,600 --> 00:37:38,560
Peking University

889
00:37:39,040 --> 00:37:40,000
has imported a new batch of books.

890
00:37:40,320 --> 00:37:41,360
If you're willing,

891
00:37:41,760 --> 00:37:44,160
I can give you the job

892
00:37:43,440 --> 00:37:44,160
of editing the catalogue.

893
00:37:44,320 --> 00:37:44,560
This way,

894
00:37:44,880 --> 00:37:47,360
you'll be able to learn from your experience.

895
00:37:47,600 --> 00:37:48,400
You will be the first to read those books.

896
00:37:48,800 --> 00:37:49,360
Thank you so much!

897
00:37:49,840 --> 00:37:50,640
Mr. Shouchang,

898
00:37:50,960 --> 00:37:52,000
can I read them now?

899
00:37:52,320 --> 00:37:52,720
Of course.

900
00:37:52,800 --> 00:37:53,600
Come.

901
00:37:53,360 --> 00:37:53,600
Let's go.

902
00:37:57,840 --> 00:37:58,480
What did you say?

903
00:37:58,560 --> 00:38:00,400
I'm saying the incident of the police arresting students,

904
00:38:00,640 --> 00:38:01,760
was a scheme planned by Zhang Fengzai,

905
00:38:01,920 --> 00:38:03,120
a student of our school.

906
00:38:03,440 --> 00:38:04,960
Sir, regarding such immoral students,

907
00:38:05,040 --> 00:38:06,480
we should expel him immediately.

908
00:38:06,800 --> 00:38:08,000
Do you have evidence?

909
00:38:08,160 --> 00:38:09,200
I am the evidence.

910
00:38:09,600 --> 00:38:10,960
I saw with my own eyes him speaking with the police.

911
00:38:11,280 --> 00:38:12,400
It was he who asked the police to come.

912
00:38:12,880 --> 00:38:14,000
Also that day we were performing,

913
00:38:14,240 --> 00:38:15,440
there were people making a scene.

914
00:38:15,840 --> 00:38:17,680
Those people were under the orders of Liu Yipin.

915
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:19,200
Everyone present witnessed it.

916
00:38:20,880 --> 00:38:22,160
He called the police over.

917
00:38:22,720 --> 00:38:23,680
It doesn't mean anything.

918
00:38:24,240 --> 00:38:25,120
He saw them fighting

919
00:38:25,360 --> 00:38:26,960
and called the police, it's a logical action.

920
00:38:27,040 --> 00:38:28,160
We were performing!

921
00:38:28,720 --> 00:38:29,840
Why would we be fighting?

922
00:38:30,240 --> 00:38:31,200
When those gangsters were making a scene,

923
00:38:31,360 --> 00:38:32,320
why did the police come?

924
00:38:32,560 --> 00:38:33,280
Why did the police come

925
00:38:33,440 --> 00:38:34,320
and arrest us?

926
00:38:34,640 --> 00:38:35,360
This is such a simple explanation.

927
00:38:35,600 --> 00:38:36,720
Why don't you understand?

928
00:38:36,880 --> 00:38:37,920
Student Xingang, Don't worry.

929
00:38:38,160 --> 00:38:39,280
What I mean is,

930
00:38:39,600 --> 00:38:40,880
we can't just base it on what you say.

931
00:38:41,280 --> 00:38:42,160
This Liu Yipin you mentioned,

932
00:38:42,480 --> 00:38:43,520
we will question him.

933
00:38:43,840 --> 00:38:44,720
If it's what you say it is,

934
00:38:44,960 --> 00:38:46,400
we will take the necessary action.

935
00:38:46,480 --> 00:38:48,240
The truth is right in front of your eyes, what more do you need?

936
00:38:48,480 --> 00:38:50,240
Sir, are you deliberately defending

937
00:38:50,400 --> 00:38:51,200
Zhang Fengzai and Liu Yipin?

938
00:38:51,920 --> 00:38:52,640
How can you speak this way?

939
00:38:53,600 --> 00:38:55,040
Everything must be evidence-based,

940
00:38:55,600 --> 00:38:57,680
I can't simply listen to your side alone.

941
00:38:58,080 --> 00:38:59,040
Other students will then think

942
00:38:59,120 --> 00:39:00,080
that I am biased towards you.

943
00:39:00,720 --> 00:39:01,520
What should I do then?

944
00:39:02,240 --> 00:39:02,960
Indeed.

945
00:39:03,280 --> 00:39:05,440
You cannot make baseless accusations.

946
00:39:06,400 --> 00:39:07,280
Student Guo Xingang,

947
00:39:08,000 --> 00:39:09,280
I remember in my class

948
00:39:09,520 --> 00:39:10,880
you frequently had arguments with Zhang Fengzai.

949
00:39:11,760 --> 00:39:14,320
You are not taking this opportunity to defame him aren't you?

950
00:39:14,480 --> 00:39:16,880
Mr. Song, you know me well.

951
00:39:17,040 --> 00:39:18,240
I will not do such things.

952
00:39:19,200 --> 00:39:20,720
I believe you wouldn't,

953
00:39:21,120 --> 00:39:22,640
but we need evidence.

954
00:39:22,880 --> 00:39:24,640
If you have evidence, we will talk.

955
00:39:25,280 --> 00:39:25,840
But...

956
00:39:26,240 --> 00:39:27,040
Teacher Song,

957
00:39:27,600 --> 00:39:30,000
did you pass those documents that I asked you to?

958
00:39:30,480 --> 00:39:33,680
Not yet, there's still some details

959
00:39:34,160 --> 00:39:36,320
that we need to finetune.

960
00:39:37,120 --> 00:39:37,680
I don't understand.

961
00:39:37,760 --> 00:39:39,040
As a librarian's assistant,

962
00:39:39,360 --> 00:39:40,960
what do you do all day?

963
00:39:42,400 --> 00:39:42,880
What's the matter?

964
00:39:43,360 --> 00:39:44,720
Student, what's wrong?

965
00:39:44,960 --> 00:39:45,920
He's saying we're too slow.

966
00:39:51,280 --> 00:39:51,760
Student,

967
00:39:52,240 --> 00:39:52,720
I apologise.

968
00:39:53,120 --> 00:39:54,640
There are too many students borrowing books today.

969
00:39:54,960 --> 00:39:55,840
Sorry to take up your time.

970
00:39:56,560 --> 00:39:57,600
You think you can placate me with an apology?

971
00:39:58,000 --> 00:39:59,200
Saying there are too many students is an excuse.

972
00:39:59,920 --> 00:40:01,520
Are you saying it is our fault for borrowing books?

973
00:40:02,160 --> 00:40:03,760
You should reflect on your actions

974
00:40:03,840 --> 00:40:05,760
and not push the blame to the students.

975
00:40:05,920 --> 00:40:06,560
Student,

976
00:40:06,800 --> 00:40:07,600
please calm down.

977
00:40:08,080 --> 00:40:09,200
That's not what I meant.

978
00:40:09,680 --> 00:40:10,240
Look,

979
00:40:10,640 --> 00:40:12,480
there really is a large number of students borrowing books today.

980
00:40:12,880 --> 00:40:13,360
We

981
00:40:13,520 --> 00:40:14,160
are a little slow in looking for the books.

982
00:40:14,880 --> 00:40:15,440
How about this,

983
00:40:15,840 --> 00:40:17,040
tell me what book you are looking for.

984
00:40:17,280 --> 00:40:17,840
I'll look for it for you.

985
00:40:18,160 --> 00:40:18,960
I'm not talking to you.

986
00:40:19,920 --> 00:40:21,920
I want to speak to Mr. Li Dazhou personally

987
00:40:22,240 --> 00:40:23,360
and make a complaint to the school.

988
00:40:28,480 --> 00:40:29,120
Mr. Chen.

989
00:40:33,280 --> 00:40:34,000
Mr. Chen.

990
00:40:35,040 --> 00:40:35,600
Mr. Chen.

991
00:40:36,160 --> 00:40:37,600
New assistant librarian,

992
00:40:39,200 --> 00:40:40,480
what's going on?

993
00:40:42,960 --> 00:40:43,680
Well,

994
00:40:43,760 --> 00:40:44,320
today,

995
00:40:44,640 --> 00:40:45,760
there are many people borrowing books.

996
00:40:46,160 --> 00:40:47,680
We are a little slow looking for the books.

997
00:40:47,920 --> 00:40:49,600
This student is getting impatient.

998
00:40:50,000 --> 00:40:50,720
You're from Hunan?

999
00:40:50,960 --> 00:40:51,360
Yes.

1000
00:40:52,000 --> 00:40:52,960
Yi Baisha's student.

1001
00:40:53,840 --> 00:40:54,240
Yes.

1002
00:40:54,560 --> 00:40:56,400
Mao Zedong, Mao Runzhi.

1003
00:40:57,520 --> 00:40:57,920
Yes.

1004
00:40:58,880 --> 00:40:59,440
Chen Duxiu,

1005
00:40:59,920 --> 00:41:00,720
nice to meet you.

1006
00:41:03,520 --> 00:41:04,240
Hello, Mr. Chen.

1007
00:41:11,440 --> 00:41:12,640
I've read your essay.

1008
00:41:13,040 --> 00:41:14,240
I really like your writing.

1009
00:41:15,440 --> 00:41:16,160
Student Fu Sinian,

1010
00:41:16,720 --> 00:41:18,480
the number of students borrowing books really is high today.

1011
00:41:18,800 --> 00:41:20,000
It is only natural that the speed is slower.

1012
00:41:20,560 --> 00:41:21,760
I don't think this situation needs to be like this.

1013
00:41:22,480 --> 00:41:23,440
He's new here,

1014
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:25,200
please be more understanding.

1015
00:41:25,680 --> 00:41:26,640
Don't nitpick.

1016
00:41:27,360 --> 00:41:27,760
Alright?

1017
00:41:28,160 --> 00:41:29,440
Now that you've said it, sir,

1018
00:41:30,240 --> 00:41:32,720
I won't be borrowing this book today then.
